City Hall will be lit Blue to celebrate&nbsp;Navy Week - Beat to Quarters
Showcasing Navy&rsquo;s importance to the Australian way of life. The Navy will celebrate its traditions and heritage through a number of events across Brisbane for Navy Week and we encourage all to come along. Join us for Beat to Quarters at King George Square. Beat to Quarters is a tradition dating back to the age of sails. It was the sound of a ships drum that would summon the Sailors to action stations when battle was imminent. Today we keep the beat to quarters tradition going to honour the courage and sacrifice of men and women that have served in the Royal Australian Navy.
This Light Up is organised by: Brisbane City Council &nbsp;
